        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.37.1-3-0001b" />
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Skyrim, July 1, '62</dateline>
               
                    <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I'm glad you are <del>ro</del> with your Father. Give him the kindest thoughts from me. I'd like to know him.</p>
                
                <p>Yours of the 28th arrived yesterday.</p> 
                
                <p>I'll leave here on July 9th with Hutchins, director of my <hi rend="caps">MU TV</hi> series next fall (The Twilight of the Sioux) We'll be in Lincoln the 10th and 11th. On the 12th I'll take a plane for Imperial where Stanley will meet me. We will
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">1</fw>
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.37.1-3_0001a"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    <note type="curatorial">Aly Collection</note>
                    
                    leave Wauneta for the Oregon Trail expedition on July 14th. About the 19th (maybe the 20th) I'll take either train or plane for Portland. (I have thought <add>this</add> might be at Green River Wyo., or near there)</p>
                
                <p>I'll let you know when to expect me and where.</p>
                
                <p>You can mail a letter to me here, if you wish, on the 4th of July, after that (on the 8th or 9th) to the Hist. Society, Lincoln
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.37.1-3_0002a"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>
                    
                    c/o Phyllis). After that <del>no <unclear/></del> mail to Wauneta, c/o Stanley Smith. I'll have letters forwarded from Wauneta to at least one place on the Oregon Trail.</p>
                
                <p>I've received the script for <hi rend="underline">The Pioneer Heritage</hi> series to be filmed in Lincoln late in August. It's for the National Educational <hi rend="caps">TV</hi>. I'll no <hi rend="underline">doubt</hi> work on that
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.37.1-3_0002b"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-4-</fw>
                    
                    while in Lincoln.</p>
                
                <p>I'm so glad you find my footnotes beneficial. I insist upon <hi rend="underline">universal lucidity</hi>. (<del>These</del><add>These</add> are hard words, but I have no time to explain.)</p>
                
                <p>Alice &amp; Cook have taken over the Christian College Horsemanship department, &amp; will <del>operate</del> operate on the College farm two miles out <del>of</del> on Hy 63 South. I do hope Alice will be happy. It's a big opportunity. This place will be used for brood mares and colts</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Love</salute> <signed>John (the well-known scholiost)</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">2</fw>
            </div1>
            
            
